title: Haymans Green (The Pete Best Band)
description:
"Haymans Green" is a 2008 album by The Pete Best Band, released by Lightyear Entertainment and distributed in the US and Canada by EMI. Pete Best plays drums, and co-wrote all of the tracks. Reviews of the album have been mixed, although almost all reviewers agree that the album sounds influenced by The Beatles, a band which Pete Best was once a member of from 1960 to 1962.


All songs written by Pete Best, Roag Best, Phil Melia and Paul Parry except where noted

1. Come With Me (Written by Pete Best, Phil Melia & Paul Parry)
2. Step Outside
3. Round and Round
4. Grey River
5. Gone
6. Dream Me Home
7. Everything I Want (Written by Pete Best, Phil Melia & Paul Parry)
8. Beat Street (Written by Pete Best, Phil Melia & Paul Parry)
9. Broken
10. Red Light
11. Haymans Green
